{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01V7eecQEFinTP1k3YDdfBy3","type":"tool_result","content":"# GitHub Issue Summary: Leave API Service Implementation\n\n## **Title**\n\"Implement leave-api service\" (Issue #1)\n\n## **Core Description**\nA production-ready Go HTTP microservice for managing employee leave requests and balance tracking, with overlap detection and state persistence.\n\n## **Working Directory**\n```\n/Users/kajendran/.asdlc/repos/default/kaj-test-18/leave-api\n```\n\n## **Key Requirements**\n\n**Service Specifications:**\n- Language: Go\n- Port: 9090\n- Storage: In-memory maps (no database required)\n- Entry point structure: `cmd/` or `main.go`\n\n**API Endpoints:**\n- `GET /health` – Service availability check\n- `GET /leave/balance?employeeId=X` – Balance by leave category\n- `GET /leave/requests?employeeId=X` – All requests for employee\n- `POST /leave/requests` – Create request with conflict validation\n- `DELETE /leave/requests/{id}?employeeId=X` – Cancel pending requests\n\n## **Functional Requirements**\n- Detect and reject overlapping leave periods (409 status)\n- Validate date ranges and required fields (400 status)\n- Support pending/approved/rejected statuses\n- Generate UUID-based request identifiers\n- Seed initial balances: emp1 (15 annual, 10 sick), emp2 (20 annual, 5 sick)\n\n## **Deliverables**\n- Modular code structure with handlers, services, models packages\n- Multi-stage Dockerfile (golang:1.21 builder → alpine:latest runtime)\n- `go.mod` with appropriate module declaration\n- `workload.yaml` for platform configuration\n- No required environment variables; hardcoded sensible defaults only\n\n## **Critical Constraints**\n- All files must remain within the specified working directory\n- No local server execution; platform handles build/deployment\n- Implement full OpenAPI specification without stubbing"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"26873e44-c89c-444e-837b-99f25d54544a","uuid":"052a3500-fcca-4a3d-bb06-6c2edcc9e45f","timestamp":"2026-04-24T09:25:16.040Z","tool_use_result":{"bytes":310628,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# GitHub Issue Summary: Leave API Service Implementation\n\n## **Title**\n\"Implement leave-api service\" (Issue #1)\n\n## **Core Description**\nA production-ready Go HTTP microservice for managing employee leave requests and balance tracking, with overlap detection and state persistence.\n\n## **Working Directory**\n```\n/Users/kajendran/.asdlc/repos/default/kaj-test-18/leave-api\n```\n\n## **Key Requirements**\n\n**Service Specifications:**\n- Language: Go\n- Port: 9090\n- Storage: In-memory maps (no database required)\n- Entry point structure: `cmd/` or `main.go`\n\n**API Endpoints:**\n- `GET /health` – Service availability check\n- `GET /leave/balance?employeeId=X` – Balance by leave category\n- `GET /leave/requests?employeeId=X` – All requests for employee\n- `POST /leave/requests` – Create request with conflict validation\n- `DELETE /leave/requests/{id}?employeeId=X` – Cancel pending requests\n\n## **Functional Requirements**\n- Detect and reject overlapping leave periods (409 status)\n- Validate date ranges and required fields (400 status)\n- Support pending/approved/rejected statuses\n- Generate UUID-based request identifiers\n- Seed initial balances: emp1 (15 annual, 10 sick), emp2 (20 annual, 5 sick)\n\n## **Deliverables**\n- Modular code structure with handlers, services, models packages\n- Multi-stage Dockerfile (golang:1.21 builder → alpine:latest runtime)\n- `go.mod` with appropriate module declaration\n- `workload.yaml` for platform configuration\n- No required environment variables; hardcoded sensible defaults only\n\n## **Critical Constraints**\n- All files must remain within the specified working directory\n- No local server execution; platform handles build/deployment\n- Implement full OpenAPI specification without stubbing","durationMs":6913,"url":"https://github.com/asdlc-repos/kaj-test-18041/issues/1"}}
